					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is peeled off towards the end. It records the setting up of an image of <hi rend="bold">Sūryadēva</hi> with 500 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold in the temple of Tiruvanantīśvaram-Uḍaiyār by (princess) <hi rend="bold">Kundavaiyār</hi>, who also endowed 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> for burning two perpetual lamps in the temple. This latter amount seems to have been invested on some land at Vilattūr. This may be a record of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
